haven’t posted in forever and here’s why.

lately i’ve been in such a funk. from leaving my apartment earlier and having the owner burst in completely unaccounted and fighting with me, to having a total breakdown for 2 weeks straight, to people in my life who ignored me knowing fully well i wasn’t ok, and to my family who literally abandoned me and did not give me a proper welcome when i moved back (because i had no choice but to move back temporarily for a month ish). the constant disrespect i had abused was astonishing, and my poor bunny was so scared. I vowed never to let this happen again. 

i was honestly so lost… and i had no choice but to pick myself back up and carry on and find myself amidst all the chaos. life somehow has always been so challenging to me, and I wish it was easier. 

I wish I can just find a nice apartment to stay in, without ANY issues. i wish i can just move out of this lifeless city for good. i wish drama didn’t follow me everywhere i went. i wish i can finally settle down with a good man who will treat me the way i deserve to be treated. and i wish i can find my joy for life again. because lately, i haven’t. and nobody tells you what depression looks like, or how it feels like, but when you wake up , do your routine, and don’t feel the slightest zest for life, something is wrong. and im so good at putting up a front and letting you guys think im ok, but it gets tiring to always have to be strong. sometimes you just have to be. and its totally ok. theres so much happening now and i need to take time for me, but i also didn’t want to keep you guys in the dark. so when im back, youll see sisi all over again, just the way she is supposed to be. until then, happy holidays everyone🤍❄️✨

thriving & glowing in 2024. and thats on periodt 💅🏼

2023 was full of unforgettable memories.

i laughed.
i cried.
i fell on love.
and i fell out of love too.
i distanced myself from anything that didn’t serve me purpose.
and refell in love with myself and what matters to me.

this year has been magical, almost like a fairytale, and if im being completely honest with you guys, it also has been heartbreaking. especially as the year ends, going through a heartbreak, losing friends you thought were there for you all your life, having no one to talk to at times and going through loneliness, was tough af to say the least.

i dont show you guys the tough moments because there are my moments. i have to go back in my shell and focus my energy on feelings those disturbing and emotional feelings, whether that means having a good cry, talking on the phone with a good friend, or eating my feelings away, its important i let my heart feel what it needs to feel. and if you know me, you know thats not an easy thing for me to do. 

without this, i wouldn’t have been able to regain focus and get back on track. i wouldn’t be thinking about what it is that i truly need, and i know exactly what that is (in love & career). 

i am thriving in my career, and i am so grateful to have a job that im passionate about. im grateful for the talent God gave me. and im grateful for the new opportunities that are coming my way this new year.

but theres so much more to me than social media.

theres music, theres love, and theres sisi unfiltered. 

so many amazing things are happening in 2024, and if i stopped myself because i was feeling down, i will never have accomplished what i have accomplished now.

its ok to take a break to heal, but remember, your dreams come first. no matter what. so get the f*** up. 

make them come true 👠
